Class Enterprise

Object
Entity
Enterprise
All Implemented Interfaces:
HasFaction, HasPosition, HasSymbol, Healable, Hittable, Positionable
public class Enterprise extends Entity implements Healable, HasFaction
Representation of the Enterprise, handles internal state for the Enterprise in our game.

    • symbol

      public String symbol()
      Provides a 3 char long String representation of the Enterprise with implicit indications for the state of:
      • Energy reserves,
      • If it has Torpedoes,
      • Shields energy levels
      .

      Energy Reserves

      • E : 1000 or more Energy Reserves (note the E can be changed out for Ë based on torpedo count)
      • e : 999 or less energy reserves (note the e can be changed out for ë based on torpedo count)

      Shields:

      • . . : indicates shields are at 0
      • - - : indicates shields are at 200 or less
      • \{ \} : indicates shields are at between 200 and 1001
      • ( ) : indicates shields are at 1001 or greater

      Torpedoes:

      If the Enterprise has any torpedoes switch out the E/e shown for the equivalent with a umlaut to signify that it has ammo. i.e E becomes Ë, e becomes ë

      Specified by:
      symbol in interface HasSymbol
      Overrides:
      symbol in class Entity
      Returns:
      a 3 char long String representation of the Enterprise with implicit indications for the state of shields, torpedo ammo and energy.
